Generate Google API Key

STEP 1: Google Developers site
1. Got to: https://developers.google.com/youtube
2. Choose: Add YouTube Data > click: Overview 
3. Click: "Google Developers Console" in "Create a project in the Google Developers Console and obtain authorization credentials so your application can submit API requests."
4. Login with Google account

STEP 2: Google Developers Console
5. At left bar, click: Home > Dashboard
6. Choose: New Project or Current Project (if already have one)
7. In Dashboard, look at API section and click "APIs overview" (at the bottom of API section)

STEP 3: APIs & Services Dashboard
8. At left bar, choose Enabled APIs & Services > + Enable APIs & Services
9. In "Search for APIs", input: Youtube
10. Landed in Youtube Data API v3 > click: Enable

STEP 4: Create Credential key (API Key)
11. Create Credentials > Fill the form
12. Choose: Public Data
13. And voila! the API Key is now served. 

(To directly check the credentials > Got Credentials at left bar > + Credentials > API Key)
==============================

Youtube API endpoints

STEP 1: Google Developers site
1. Got to: https://developers.google.com/youtube
2. Choose: Add YouTube Data > click: Reference 
3. At left bar: The list of Youtube endpoints

STEP 2: Endpoints
4. To get subscribers number choose "Channels" > Overview
5. Go to statistics" > "subscriberCount"
6. To get profile picture choose "Channels" > Overview
7. Go to   "snippet" > "thumbnails" > "url"

STEP 3: Videos
8. To get videos choose "Search" > Overview
9. Got ot "id" > "videoId"

==============================

